\par }{\insrsid4016719\charrsid31649 
\par The application is supported by the affidavit of one Stephen Kasenge, the Audit and Compliance Manager of the applicant Bank.  The respondents also filed affidavits through Clive Mutiso, the 1}{\super\insrsid4016719\charrsid31649 st}{
\insrsid4016719\charrsid31649  respondent herein and Richard John Lynton Tucker, a Director in the 3}{\super\insrsid4016719\charrsid31649 rd}{\insrsid4016719\charrsid31649  respondent.
\par 
\par }{\i\insrsid4016719\charrsid31649 Representations:
\par }{\insrsid4016719\charrsid31649 Mr. Faisal Mukasa for the applicant.
\par Mr. Augustine Kibuuka-Musoke for the respondents.
\par 
\par The grounds on which the application is based, according to the affidavit of Stephen Kasenge, are that
 the respondents intend to remove or dispose of the properties listed herein with a view to defraud the applicant from whom the first and second respondents fraudulently obtained advance payments against uncleared effects.}{\insrsid15543681\charrsid31649 
  The deponent states that the app
licant will suffer irreparable injury if the land is alienated, transferred or disposed of.  Before the hearing date, I went through the pleadings.  When the application came up for hearing, the applicant sought to apply for adjournment to file a rejoinde
r to the affidavit in reply.}{\insrsid4016719\charrsid31649 
\par }{\insrsid6893737\charrsid31649 
\par I was of the view that this application could be disposed of on the basis of the available pleadings.  }{\insrsid13924983\charrsid31649 Accordingly, I adjourned the application for a ruling on the matter.  Hence this ruling.}{
\insrsid6893737\charrsid31649 
\par }{\insrsid13924983\charrsid31649 
\par In paragraph 9 of Mr. Kasenge\rquote s affidavit, he avers:
\par }\pard \qj \li1122\ri1034\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin1034\lin1122\itap0\pararsid31649 {\b\i\insrsid13924983\charrsid31649 \'93
